  "text": "PROOF. (Sketch) Closure under target homomorphisms can be shown by a straightforward formula induction. That nested s-t tgd mappings admit universal solutions and allow for conjunctive query rewriting follows from the fact that they can be translated into SO tgds [CITATION_1] , and the latter admit universal solutions [CITATION_2] and allow for conjunctive query rewriting (Proposition 2.4). QUESTION 3.14. Is it the case that a schema mapping is definable by a finite set of nested s-t tgds if and only if it is closed under target homomorphisms, admits universal solutions, and allows for conjunctive query rewriting?",
